<article class="blog--container blog-preview">
<h2 class="blog--title">
<a href="/blog/2010/11/20/spring-android-1-0-0-m1-released">Spring Android 1.0.0.M1 Released</a>
</h2>
<header class="meta-data--container">
<div class="meta-data--item desktop-only">
<div class="meta-data--icon icon blog-icon releases"></div>
<a class="category" href="/blog/category/releases">Releases</a>
</div>
<div class="meta-data--item">
<img class="meta-data--icon" src="https://gravatar.com/avatar/55c978494c708e62f4b76bde1e0dcc19?s=20&amp;d=mm" />
<a class="author" href="/team/rclarkson">Roy Clarkson</a>
</div>
<div class="meta-data--item">
<div class="meta-data--icon icon blog-icon calendar"></div>
<time class="date" pubdate="" datetime="2010-11-20 00:22:00.0">November 20, 2010</time>
</div>
<div class="meta-data--item">
<div class="meta-data--icon icon blog-icon comments"></div>
<a class="comments" data-disqus-identifier="739" href="/blog/2010/11/20/spring-android-1-0-0-m1-released#disqus_thread">
</a></div>
</header>
<section class="blog--post desktop-only">
<div><p>Dear Spring Community,</p>
<p>We are pleased to announce that the first milestone release of the <a href="http://www.springsource.org/spring-android">Spring Android</a> project is now available!</p>
<p>Spring Android supports usage of the Spring Framework in a Android environment. The defining feature of the 1.0.0.M1 release is RestTemplate support that provides a robust REST client to use in native Android applications. </p>
<p>To get you started, Keith has posted a <a target="_blank" href="http://blog.springsource.com/2010/11/19/spring-into-mobile-application-development/">Spring into Mobile Application Development</a> blog, which provides insight into the project.</p>
<p>This milestone is the first in an exciting road ahead. If you're building native Android applications that communicate with Spring web apps, we invite you to join us in the development of the Spring Android project!</p>
</div>
</section>
<a class="blog-preview--readmore desktop-only" href="/blog/2010/11/20/spring-android-1-0-0-m1-released">
